node.text: The Nobu Collection’s portfolio of luxurious expressions of Japanese-inspired modern minimalism has stretched wide and far – from London to Malibu and everywhere in between – and now Nobu has claimed an address on a historic street of Poland’s capital, Warsaw. Nobu Hotels are renown for their graceful contemporary ryokan-inspired civility superimposed across a wide variety of urban landscapes. The @nobuhotelwarsaw is arguably the collection’s most dramatic expression of this design philosophy, with an artful minimalism framing the historic art-deco style throughout the hotel’s 117 rooms. \\\ Read more about the Nobu Hotel Warsaw and book your next stay at the link in bio. 🔗

node.text: Bringing you another favorite from the #DestinationDesign archives, this time from California’s Alpine Meadows Valley. What began as a simple 1970s alpine cabin in the Bear Creek neighborhood was been given the full @heathceramics treatment by the couple behind the Californian homewares brand, Catherine Bailey and Robin Petravic. With deep respect for the original design by Tahoe architect Charles O. Matcham, Catherine and Robin set about expertly renovating and appointing the space as a personal family retreat. \\\ Read more about the Heath House at the link in bio. 🔗

node.text: The revolution unfolding across the automotive industry is well documented with new electric offerings rolling out nearly every month. But there’s also a design renaissance happening within the motorcycle category as new manufacturers of electric bikes emerge. Case in point: the DAB Motor CONCEPT-E arrives as the company’s first electric motorcycle with a sleek and minimalist silhouette that silently redefines the commuter bike with supermoto styling. \\\ Read more about the CONCEPT-E at the link in bio. 🔗

node.text: If you’re ready to pack your bags and get away, consider Mexico. Located in Aldea Zama, Villa Tulum is only a few short minutes away from the heart of Tulum and Mexico's famous beaches, making it perfect for those who want privacy without complete seclusion. The modern interior begins with white walls, floors and ceilings that create a calm, soothing backdrop. Black framed windows punctuate, while the furnishings boast clean lines and neutral hues for an elegant yet comfortable vacation retreat. This beautiful rental exudes minimalist luxury and maximum relaxation. \\\ Read more about the Villa Tulum and how to rent the space for your next beach getaway at the link in bio. 🔗

node.text: @brochnerhotels’ first hotel outside of Copenhagen is not really a hotel at all, nor is it a hostel by normal measures. The brand is creating a hybrid hospitality concept that sits right in the middle. The new @book1_designhostel in Aarhus has all the classic hostel elements like bunk beds, laundry facilities and ping pong tables, as well as luxury hotel elements such as private rooms and suites, a sauna and unique design details. BOOK1 is perfect for the modern traveler who is looking for extraordinary experiences in hospitality and gastronomy without sacrificing budget. \\\ Read more about the BOOK1 Design Hostel in the latest #DestinationDesign at the link in bio. 🔗

node.text: Another from the #DestinationDesign archives, the Kumaon is a minimalist hotel designed by architect Pradeep Kodikara and Jineshi Samaraweera of @zowa_architects that offers its guests an unparalleled, immersive experience in nature. With 10 luxury suites, a library, a sun lounge and a gourmet restaurant, guests will no doubt find a new kind of peace amongst the mountains, valleys, forests and lakes. \\\ Read more about the Kumaon at the link in bio. 🔗

node.text: This week over on @designmilk: Vipp might have gotten their start with a pedal-operated trash bin, but over the last 80 years the Danish brand has grown to include just about any product one might possibly need in their home. In recent years, they’ve expanded beyond objects to design full kitchens and even a few hotels, including their latest, the @vipp Farmhouse. Located on the Danish island of Lolland in a 100-acre forest, Vipp’s 4th hotel destination has launched as a one-room hotel housed within a traditional Danish farmhouse. \\\ Read more about the Vipp Farmhouse at the link in bio. 🔗

node.text: Starting in the late 1800s, Mexico City’s center began a rapid and far-reaching period of industrialization that would transform the city’s landscape. The urban expansion would eventually compel an upper class exodus, resulting in numerous former multi-storied residences of the wealthy to be sold or abandoned, soon to be adopted and adapted into what would become to be known as vecindades – affordable multi-family tenements divided into individual rooms. The Círculo Mexicano is one such building, a vecindad given a serene modern makeover by architectural firm, @ambrosietchegaray. \\\ Learn more about the Círculo Mexicano in the latest #DestinationDesign at the link in bio. 🔗

node.text: We can feel island life beckoning 🍹 so we dug deep into the archives for this feature on the @shorelinehotel Waikiki. An explosion of neon and nature, this 56,000-square-foot, 135-room boutique hotel takes the concept of Hawaiian-inspired design and transforms it into a modern day interpretation that still feels authentic. \\\ Read more about the Shoreline Waikiki and get the deets on how to book your stay at the link in bio. 🔗

node.text: This week on @designmilk: We've had travel on the brain recently - meaning we've been daydreaming, scheming and spending irresponsible amounts of time researching and planning trips that we may or may not ever take. Editorial director Caroline Williamson (@element75) has been especially fixated on a tour of Italy. "Take me to the Amalfi Coast, Venice, Capri, Rome, Tuscany… you get the point! Speaking of Tuscany, this dream-worthy house in the middle of the Chianti region landed on my radar and it will forever live in my brain now." \\\ At the link in bio, read about Casa Morelli: a Tuscan farmhouse-inspired modern retreat available to rent for your next Italian vacay.
